.com/blogs/news/the-best-dashcam-with-parking-mode" target="_self">parking monitor function</a>, which requires continuous power even when your car is turned off. Although hardwiring may be slightly more complex than the basic installation, we will guide you through three different scenarios based on the type of dash cam&nbsp;hardwire kits available, ensuring you can take full advantage of your dash cam's capabilities.</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hiwPVj bcyuPn pf-90_"><i class="sc-faUpoM cTsgqM pf-91_ pfa pfa-star" data-pf-type="Icon"></i>Single Fuse Hardwire Kit</h3><p class="sc-ehCJOs iphVAH pf-92_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The single fuse hardwire kit comes with the product package. It consists of three wires: an earth cord, an ACC wire (red), and a BATT wire (yellow). 

</p><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0722/1077/6353/files/3_16056993-eb26-4fb9-8290-198336c34f41_500x.jpg?v=1691742872" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0722/1077/6353/files/3_16056993-eb26-4fb9-8290-198336c34f41.jpg?v=1691742872 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0722/1077/6353/files/3_16056993-eb26-4fb9-8290-198336c34f41_1000x.jpg?v=1691742872 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0722/1077/6353/files/3_16056993-eb26-4fb9-8290-198336c34f41_500x.jpg?v=1691742872 320w" width="1200" height="1200" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, 320px" loading="lazy" alt="single fuse hardwire kit" title="single fuse hardwire kit" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jOxtWs ffIUiZ pf-94_"/><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-dYtuZ bTisNR pf-95_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAWBJg ciQrUe pf-96_"><b>Earth Cord</b>: This wire is used to connect to the ground bolt in your vehicle. It ensures proper grounding for the dash cam.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAWBJg ciQrUe pf-98_"><b><span style="color: rgb(240, 102, 102);">ACC Wire</span></b>: The ACC wire provides power to the dash cam when the ignition is turned on. It connects to a fuse slot that supplies power when the accessory or ignition is active.  </li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAWBJg ciQrUe pf-100_"><b><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 102);"></span></b><span style="color: rgb(255, 194, 102);"><b>BATT Wire</b>:</span> The BATT wire provides constant power to the dash cam, even when the ignition is off. It connects to a fuse slot labeled "Battery," "Constant," or "Always-On." </li></ul><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0722/1077/6353/files/3_29f49334-278a-4771-94f0-ea8ff1d25142_500x.jpg?v=1691742872" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0722/1077/6353/files/3_29f49334-278a-4771-94f0-ea8ff1d25142.jpg?v=1691742872 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0722/1077/6353/files/3_29f49334-278a-4771-94f0-ea8ff1d25142_1000x.jpg?v=1691742872 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0722/1077/6353/files/3_29f49334-278a-4771-94f0-ea8ff1d25142_500x.jpg?v=1691742872 320w" width="1200" height="1200" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, 320px" loading="lazy" alt="how to hardwire" title="how to hardwire" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jOxtWs ffIUiZ pf-102_"/></div></div></div><div class="sc-efQSVx kdrjec pf-103_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fvpsdx eVTiRY pf-104_"><p class="sc-ehCJOs iphVAH pf-105_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Begin by locating the fuse box in your vehicle and identifying appropriate empty fuse slots. But before inserting the wire, it's important to ensure that this hardwire kit&nbsp;is compatible with your vehicle's fuse box. You can do this by checking the wire's specifications and comparing them to the fuse box requirements</p><p class="sc-ehCJOs iphVAH pf-107_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Take off the fuse box cover, and there will be some reference on the cover, or you can find in the vehicle 's manual. The diagram will indicate the various fuse slots and their functions. For example, you have to avoid the fuses in charge of airbags, stability control programs, horns, indicators, looking for empty fuses that deal with components like the AC, radio, sunroof, boot opener. 

</p><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0722/1077/6353/files/4_448c3ad0-467c-420a-ad6f-194385fa49b6_500x.jpg?v=1691742872" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0722/1077/6353/files/4_448c3ad0-467c-420a-ad6f-194385fa49b6.jpg?v=1691742872 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0722/1077/6353/files/4_448c3ad0-467c-420a-ad6f-194385fa49b6_1000x.jpg?v=1691742872 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0722/1077/6353/files/4_448c3ad0-467c-420a-ad6f-194385fa49b6_500x.jpg?v=1691742872 320w" width="1200" height="1200" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, 320px" loading="lazy" alt="locate fuse box " title="locate fuse box " data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jOxtWs ffIUiZ pf-109_"/><p class="sc-ehCJOs iphVAH pf-110_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">For added assurance, you can use a multimeter or a circuit tester to verify that the identified empty slots have power when the ignition is on (for the ACC wire) or at all times (for the BATT wire). This step ensures that the chosen slots are suitable for connecting your dash cam's power cables.
<br><br>For the earth cord, inspect the area near the fuse box: Often, you can find grounding points near the fuse box or under the dashboard. 
 

